{"config":{"indexing":"full","lang":["en"],"min_search_length":3,"prebuild_index":true,"separator":"[\\s\\-]+"},"docs":[{"location":"","text":"Path to a TCer Welcome to Path to a TCer! This guide is designed to introduce college students to the exciting world of technical writing using modern tools like Git, GitHub, Markdown, and MkDocs. Learn how to manage documentation like code, collaborate effectively, and create professional, user-friendly documents.","title":"Welcome"},{"location":"#path-to-a-tcer","text":"Welcome to Path to a TCer! This guide is designed to introduce college students to the exciting world of technical writing using modern tools like Git, GitHub, Markdown, and MkDocs. Learn how to manage documentation like code, collaborate effectively, and create professional, user-friendly documents.","title":"Path to a TCer"},{"location":"introduction/","text":"Welcome to the Program What is technical writing? Why is \"doc-like-code\" important? Writing and managing documents like code ensures better collaboration, version control, and automation. Program Goals: Teach you Git and GitHub. Get you comfortable using Markdown for documentation. Help you build your own documentation website with MkDocs.","title":"Introduction"},{"location":"introduction/#welcome-to-the-program","text":"What is technical writing? Why is \"doc-like-code\" important? Writing and managing documents like code ensures better collaboration, version control, and automation. Program Goals: Teach you Git and GitHub. Get you comfortable using Markdown for documentation. Help you build your own documentation website with MkDocs.","title":"Welcome to the Program"},{"location":"prerequisites/","text":"Tools & Knowledge Needed Basic Computer Knowledge: Using files, folders, and terminals. Tools to Install: Git: A version control system. MkDocs: A tool for building documentation websites. A text editor like VS Code.","title":"Prerequisites"},{"location":"prerequisites/#tools-knowledge-needed","text":"Basic Computer Knowledge: Using files, folders, and terminals. Tools to Install: Git: A version control system. MkDocs: A tool for building documentation websites. A text editor like VS Code.","title":"Tools &amp; Knowledge Needed"},{"location":"resources/","text":"Additional Learning Resources Git Documentation GitHub Guides MkDocs Documentation Free Markdown Editors: Typora, Obsidian, VS Code.","title":"Resources"},{"location":"resources/#additional-learning-resources","text":"Git Documentation GitHub Guides MkDocs Documentation Free Markdown Editors: Typora, Obsidian, VS Code.","title":"Additional Learning Resources"},{"location":"git-and-github/basics/","text":"Understanding Git and GitHub What is Git? Git is like a time machine for your files. It helps you track changes, go back to previous versions, and collaborate with others. What is GitHub? GitHub is like a social media site for coders and writers where your Git files live in the cloud.","title":"What is Git&GitHub"},{"location":"git-and-github/basics/#understanding-git-and-github","text":"What is Git? Git is like a time machine for your files. It helps you track changes, go back to previous versions, and collaborate with others. What is GitHub? GitHub is like a social media site for coders and writers where your Git files live in the cloud.","title":"Understanding Git and GitHub"},{"location":"git-and-github/collaboration/","text":"Using GitHub for Collaboration Create a repository. Clone it to your computer. Make changes and push them. Use Pull Requests to collaborate and review work.","title":"Why to use"},{"location":"git-and-github/collaboration/#using-github-for-collaboration","text":"Create a repository. Clone it to your computer. Make changes and push them. Use Pull Requests to collaborate and review work.","title":"Using GitHub for Collaboration"},{"location":"git-and-github/commands/","text":"Common Git Commands Cheat Sheet Command What it Does git init Start a Git project in your folder. git add . Add files to be tracked by Git. git commit -m \"msg\" Save changes with a message. git push Send changes to GitHub.","title":"How to use"},{"location":"git-and-github/commands/#common-git-commands-cheat-sheet","text":"Command What it Does git init Start a Git project in your folder. git add . Add files to be tracked by Git. git commit -m \"msg\" Save changes with a message. git push Send changes to GitHub.","title":"Common Git Commands Cheat Sheet"},{"location":"markdown/examples/","text":"Hands-on Markdown Examples Try writing:","title":"Why to use"},{"location":"markdown/examples/#hands-on-markdown-examples","text":"Try writing:","title":"Hands-on Markdown Examples"},{"location":"markdown/formatting/","text":"Formatting Text with Markdown Headings: # Heading 1, ## Heading 2 Lists: - Item for bullet points 1. Item for numbered lists","title":"How to use"},{"location":"markdown/formatting/#formatting-text-with-markdown","text":"Headings: # Heading 1, ## Heading 2 Lists: - Item for bullet points 1. Item for numbered lists","title":"Formatting Text with Markdown"},{"location":"markdown/intro/","text":"Introduction to Markdown Markdown is a simple way to write formatted text that looks great online. You can: Add bold and italic text. Create bullet lists. Link to websites.","title":"What is Markdown"},{"location":"markdown/intro/#introduction-to-markdown","text":"Markdown is a simple way to write formatted text that looks great online. You can: Add bold and italic text. Create bullet lists. Link to websites.","title":"Introduction to Markdown"},{"location":"mkdocs/customization/","text":"","title":"Customization"},{"location":"mkdocs/intro/","text":"What is MkDocs? MkDocs is a tool to turn Markdown files into a simple, professional website.","title":"What is MkDocs"},{"location":"mkdocs/intro/#what-is-mkdocs","text":"MkDocs is a tool to turn Markdown files into a simple, professional website.","title":"What is MkDocs?"},{"location":"mkdocs/setup/","text":"","title":"How to use"},{"location":"workflows/best-practice/","text":"Best Practices for Doc-Like-Code Keep files simple and clear. Use meaningful commit messages. Regularly review and update content.","title":"Practice"},{"location":"workflows/best-practice/#best-practices-for-doc-like-code","text":"Keep files simple and clear. Use meaningful commit messages. Regularly review and update content.","title":"Best Practices for Doc-Like-Code"},{"location":"workflows/doc-like-code/","text":"What is Doc-Like-Code? Doc-like-code means writing and managing documentation like software: Using Git for version control. Collaborating on GitHub. Automating with CI/CD.","title":"Doc-like-code"},{"location":"workflows/doc-like-code/#what-is-doc-like-code","text":"Doc-like-code means writing and managing documentation like software: Using Git for version control. Collaborating on GitHub. Automating with CI/CD.","title":"What is Doc-Like-Code?"},{"location":"workflows/example-workflow/","text":"Doc-Like-Code Workflow Example Write in Markdown. Save and version control in Git. Push to GitHub. Build the site with MkDocs.","title":"Example"},{"location":"workflows/example-workflow/#doc-like-code-workflow-example","text":"Write in Markdown. Save and version control in Git. Push to GitHub. Build the site with MkDocs.","title":"Doc-Like-Code Workflow Example"}],"index":{"fieldVectors":[["title/",[0,2.155]],["text/",[0,1.283,1,2.421,2,2.421,3,1.432,4,1.868,5,1.868,6,1.868,7,1.868,8,1.868,9,1.868,10,1.432,11,0.674,12,0.383,13,1.868,14,1.053,15,0.383,16,0.424,17,0.383,18,0.564,19,1.432,20,1.159,21,1.201,22,0.468,23,0.736,24,1.868,25,1.159,26,1.432,27,1.868,28,1.868]],["title/#path-to-a-tcer",[1,2.151,2,2.151]],["text/#path-to-a-tcer",[0,1.33,1,1.677,2,1.677,3,1.484,4,1.936,5,1.936,6,1.936,7,1.936,8,1.936,9,1.936,10,1.484,11,0.698,12,0.397,13,1.936,14,1.091,15,0.397,16,0.44,17,0.397,18,0.584,19,1.484,20,1.201,21,1.234,22,0.485,23,0.763,24,1.936,25,1.201,26,1.484,27,1.936,28,1.936]],["title/introd